    "comment": "Rationale: The study shows the existence of a synaptically localized ATG-9 pool that undergoes exo-endocytosis and localizes at a subset of synaptic vesicles in C. elegans. The exo-endocytosis of ATG-9 is important for synaptic authopagy.\nAuthors also show that ATG9A localizes at presynapses in mammalian synapses (Fig 6a-c, g-i; Fig 7b-c).. Experimental description: They used transgenic animals expressing ATG-9::GFP. The antibody against Atg9A (ab108338) is KO-validated.",
